<li id="cite_note-Picouet201996-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint">↑ <sup><a href="#cite_ref-Picouet201996_5-0">a</a> <a href="#cite_ref-Picouet201996_5-1">b</a> et <a href="#cite_ref-Picouet201996_5-2">c</a></sup> </span><span class="reference-text"><a href="#Picouet2019">Picouet 2019</a>, <abbr class="abbr" title="page(s)">p.</abbr>&#160;96. </span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-6">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text">Deetz Ch. &amp; Adams, O., <i>Elements of Map Projection</i>, 5th ed, 1945, p; 35, <span class="citation not_fr_quote" lang="en">«&#160;<span class="italique">In this mathematical transformation, Mercator did not employ a tangent cylinder nor is it ever employed in this projection. This conception did not originate with him, but is a later invention.</span>&#160;»</span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-7">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text"> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://quod.lib.umich.edu/e/eebo/A67154.0001.001?view=toc">Lire en ligne</a></span>
